text.section:
The Commission may exempt a supervisee wholly or partly from the fee assessed under subsection (b) of this section if:
the supervisee has diligently attempted but has been unable to obtain employment that provides sufficient income for the supervisee to pay the fee;
the supervisee is a student in a school, college, or university or is enrolled in a course of vocational or technical training designed to prepare the supervisee for gainful employment; and
the institution in which the supervisee is enrolled supplies certification of student status to the Commission;
the supervisee has a disability that limits possible employment, as determined by a physical or psychological examination that the Commission accepts or orders;
the supervisee is responsible for the support of dependents and the payment of the fee constitutes an undue hardship on the supervisee; or
other extenuating circumstances exist.
